    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>
                <p>Many many thanks for y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> kind Letter of may 5<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. The number of patients cured &amp;c in y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> infirmary is the thing wanted. If you can get at
                        <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0160">Sir James Dalrimples
                            collection</title></bibl> be so good as to transcribe from p.271.
                        <persName ref="pe0573">King Williamâ€™s</persName> charter to <placeName ref="pl0651">Iona</placeName>.<note type="editorial">See <bibl type="editorial">Pennant, <title ref="bi0008"><hi rend="italic">A Tour
                                    in Scotland and Voyage to the Hebrides</hi></title> (1774),
                                <biblScope unit="page">p.292</biblScope></bibl>. Pennant appears to
                        be checking his sources prior to the appearance of the second edition of
                            <bibl type="editorial"><title ref="bi0009"><hi rend="italic">A Tour in
                                    Scotland and Voyage to the Hebrides, 1772 Part
                            I</hi></title></bibl> in 1776.</note> if not too long. if so only an
                    abridgement. I hope <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                        Low</persName> &amp; you are happy together. Pray deliver the inclosed to
                        <persName ref="pe0158">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Macintyre</persName>
                    &amp; the other Please to put in the post for by omission of <placeName ref="pl0705"><hi rend="underline">N. Br.</hi></placeName> on the frank, I
                    fear it will not from hence find its way.</p>
                <closer><salute>I am Dear Sir with <lb/>true regard yrs</salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">T Pennant</persName></signed>
                <dateline>May 28<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1775.</dateline></closer>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p><address>
                        <addrLine>To</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Paton</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Custom hou<gap reason="damage" unit="lines" atLeast="1" atMost="2"/></addrLine>
                    </address></p>
                <p>W.P.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
